Review Title: 10/10 for the Hyatt Regency ATL - 0/0 for Downtown Atlanta
Negative Reviews: scammers, Panhandlers and crooks on the streets.. (Not your fault)
Positive Reviews:
Good day, I have been in the hotel industry sine 1996 and I am a GM with Sonesta Hotels. My wife originally booked our stay at the Fairfield Inn downtown ATL. What a disaster. Was expected to park 2 blocks away and walk through a war zone. Hotel was run down, homeless laid out in front of building etc.. We never even made it out of the vehicle before we started looking for another place to stay. My kids and I did not feel safe at all so we went on an opaque site and found the Hyatt Regency! WHAT A DIFFERENCE. The property was in excellent shape, staff was amazing and we had an amazing time. I am shocked how much the city has changed since my last trip back in 2013. The only negative comment would be the aggressive panhandlers that run the streets in the immediate area. There was plenty of police presence but at no time did I feel safe. My kids and I were hassled for money every single time we stepped out of the building. Sad, such a beautiful city has turned into what it has. 
I will definitely be back to stay at another Hyatt. We love the brand. Stayed at many Hyatt Place back in the day when my kids were playing travel hockey.. As a manager with Sonesta, it's hard to select another brand but you left a great impression on us. Kudos to your staff!
Room Type: Double Room with Two Double Beds

Review Title: 10/10 for the Hyatt Regency ATL - 0/0 for Downtown Atlanta
Negative Reviews: scammers, Panhandlers and crooks on the streets.. (Not your fault)
Positive Reviews:
Good day, I have been in the hotel industry sine 1996 and I am a GM with Sonesta Hotels. My wife originally booked our stay at the Fairfield Inn downtown ATL. What a disaster. Was expected to park 2 blocks away and walk through a war zone. Hotel was run down, homeless laid out in front of building etc.. We never even made it out of the vehicle before we started looking for another place to stay. My kids and I did not feel safe at all so we went on an opaque site and found the Hyatt Regency! WHAT A DIFFERENCE. The property was in excellent shape, staff was amazing and we had an amazing time. I am shocked how much the city has changed since my last trip back in 2013. The only negative comment would be the aggressive panhandlers that run the streets in the immediate area. There was plenty of police presence but at no time did I feel safe. My kids and I were hassled for money every single time we stepped out of the building. Sad, such a beautiful city has turned into what it has. 
I will definitely be back to stay at another Hyatt. We love the brand. Stayed at many Hyatt Place back in the day when my kids were playing travel hockey.. As a manager with Sonesta, it's hard to select another brand but you left a great impression on us. Kudos to your staff!
Room Type: Double Room with Two Double Beds

Review Title: Excellent accommodations with easy parking, dining, and entertainment options in area
Negative Reviews: The booking originally inclined us to believe there was a bathtub but there was only a shower. The room was spacious, clean, and comfortable but was also an adjoining room which we were not aware of prior. This didn't negatively impact the trip no more than staying during any event as such would do, but in the case of privacy or intimacy concerns it could pose an issue comparable to other offerings. Engineering was also sent to our room in error at one point and attempted to open the door unannounced with no notice from the front desk which was very awkward and somewhat unsettling. I did find it hard at times to reach guest services as well, but this again, could be expected during peak event times. Parking was also full and when calling prior to confirm we were not advised of the same affiliated parking locations that had shuttle services that we were notified of upon checking in. This could have been remedied by the staff when inquiring upon our call prior to checking in, but the numerous locations close by made it easy to circumvent. Overall none of these critiques would impact my recommendation or choice to stay again as we enjoyed the hotel immensely regardless.

Negative Reviews:
The experience I had at this hotel for my birthday was a complete letdown. From the moment I arrived, disappointment was the theme of the day. The room I had initially booked was suddenly "unavailable," which I reluctantly accepted. But as if that wasn't enough, the room we were given in exchange lacked the promised Chromecast ‚Äì a feature that had been heavily advertised in their guides and on the TV. So much for using the screen mirror function. The live channels were trash, no games. Adding to the misery, the air conditioning in the room proved to be yet another source of frustration. On a night that should have been about rest and celebration, I found myself waking up in a pool of sweat due to the malfunctioning AC.

 But wait, it gets better (or worse). The room service, which conveniently claimed to be "closed" for basic requests like extra towels, magically sprang to life for anything you were willing to shell out money for from their restaurant. This blatant disregard for the simplest guest needs left me not only frustrated but utterly disillusioned.

The valet service turned out to be a waste of time and money. Gone were the hopes of the usual convenience where you could simply request your car from your room through a call or text. Instead, this hotel had me trudging down to the basement and deal with a cashier every time I needed my car (cashiers were nice!). Not once, but twice, I found myself in a situation where the valet was seemingly MIA, leaving me to wonder if they had any clue about their own service. When the car finally arrived, it was speeding around the corner like a cameo from a Fast 5 movie.
Even the shared microwave in the market area managed to embody the hotel's overall lack of care. When I dared to inquire about the possibility of other microwaves, the staff responded with baffling uncertainty. If you're just looking for a place to sleep that's close to downtown, this is it. O

With it being our honeymoon, we decided to upgrade to a king room with a balcony upon arrival (don't bother, the balcony is a stone plank with no place to sit). Our room had an adjoining room which we thought was a bit strange and unfortunately meant that we were awake all night while they had a party and smoked weed which filtered really strongly onto our side. The next morning I asked reception for a room move. They said it wasn't as simple as that and they would need me to go with security up to the problem room for an inspection to prove that what I was saying was true. I  said I really didn't want any trouble and would rather just move rooms. I was told they are a busy hotel and they couldn't give me the equivalent room. I said that was ok and we would accept our original pre-upgraded room and a reimbursement of the difference - to which I was told 'I can't see why we would be reimbursing you for anything, its you who is asking to move...'. I couldn't believe it. We finally agreed on an afternoon move to a smaller room but when we came to reception in the afternoon to get the key, we had to start all over again as the original person had forgotten to put any notes on our file. We were eventually relocated to a room which was poor to say the least - the 'balcony' looked into 2 other rooms and over the car port so you get all the noise of cars pulling up to pick up/drop people off, the smoke alarm went off every time we had a shower because the bathroom fan didn't work and we received several phone calls about room service we didn't order. 

The restaurant is filthy and service is the slowest I've ever seen (we waited 45 minute for our card and cheque to be taken before finally giving up and charging it to the room just so we could leave). 

Overall, this hotel is a disaster and should be avoided.
